<paragraph blockId="5.[163,780,1753,1898]" lastBlockId="5.[827,1444,197,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
This clade grouped the samples from the morphospecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1847" box="[212,326,1784,1806]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="durieui">
<emphasis box="[212,326,1784,1806]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. durieui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spengler" authorityYear="1793" box="[381,486,1784,1806]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis box="[381,486,1784,1806]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister lineages (
<figureCitation box="[702,765,1784,1806]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[145,224,1790,1812]" captionTargetBox="[307,1264,658,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-241@4.[306,1264,657,1751]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian tree reconstruction based on the two mitochondrial genes analysed. Values on the branches indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities, ML and MP bootstrap values. Results from the species delimitation analyses are also shown in this figure (green: M-PTP with a Bayesian tree; red: M-PTP with an ML tree; blue: bGMYC analysis). Names for the currently recognized morphospecies are also indicated in the phylogenetic tree." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713991/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1847" box="[218,339,1814,1836]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="durieui">
<emphasis box="[218,339,1814,1836]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. durieui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage only included samples from 
<collectingCountry box="[163,256,1845,1867]" name="Tunisia" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
and consisted of five different haplotypes among the specimens from the three rivers sampled. Distinct haplotypes were present in each river, but the most frequent haplotype was shared among specimens from the Ziatine and El Maaden rivers (Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation box="[977,1055,289,311]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[145,224,1790,1812]" captionTargetBox="[307,1264,658,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-241@4.[306,1264,657,1751]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian tree reconstruction based on the two mitochondrial genes analysed. Values on the branches indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities, ML and MP bootstrap values. Results from the species delimitation analyses are also shown in this figure (green: M-PTP with a Bayesian tree; red: M-PTP with an ML tree; blue: bGMYC analysis). Names for the currently recognized morphospecies are also indicated in the phylogenetic tree." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713991/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Fig. S1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[827,1444,197,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1847" box="[1056,1178,320,341]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="durieui">
<emphasis box="[1056,1178,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. durieui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens were elongated with an intermediate shape between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1819" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mancus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. mancus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[934,1082,382,403]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pictorum">
<emphasis box="[934,1082,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. pictorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and probably impossible to distinguish in the absence of geographical information. There were also rounded morphotypes similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spengler" authorityYear="1793" box="[827,937,473,495]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis box="[827,937,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in the case of El Maaden (
<bibRefCitation author="Khalloufi N &amp; Toledo C &amp; Machordom A &amp; Boumaiza M &amp; Araujo R" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref12779" refString="Khalloufi N, Toledo C. Machordom A, Boumaiza M, Araujo R. 2011. The unionids of Tunisia: taxonomy and phylogenetic relationships, with redescription of Unio ravoisieri Deshayes, 1847 and U. durieui Deshayes, 1847. Journal of Molluscan Studies 77: 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2011">
Khalloufi 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5). This species was not found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1350,1443,504,525]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Morocco</collectingCountry>
but is present in 
<collectingCountry box="[1019,1106,534,556]" name="Tunisia" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1246,534,556]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Algeria</collectingCountry>
to the east of the Moulouya River (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1087,565,587]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,226,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[209,1360,197,981]" captionTargetId="figure-473@6.[207,1362,195,982]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Schematic distribution of the Unio species in the Western Palaearctic. Points indicate the general vicinity of sampled localities. See Supporting Information, Table S1 for details." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713993/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[827,1444,197,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
For the morphospecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spengler" authorityYear="1793" box="[1126,1236,596,617]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Unio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1236,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">U. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we obtained two clearly separated groups (genetic distance of 2.03%, 
<tableCitation box="[827,910,657,679]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="7.[143,207,613,635]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Table 1. COI genetic distances between different lineages" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/A8936632FFC0D52C9E985505FBCF036F" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" tableUuid="A8936632FFC0D52C9E985505FBCF036F">Table 1</tableCitation>
): one representing haplotypes from the Iberian Peninsula (Barbate River) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1192,1289,688,709]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, and another consisting of Tunisian haplotypes (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1299,718,740]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,226,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[209,1360,197,981]" captionTargetId="figure-473@6.[207,1362,195,982]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Schematic distribution of the Unio species in the Western Palaearctic. Points indicate the general vicinity of sampled localities. See Supporting Information, Table S1 for details." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713993/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
; Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation box="[981,1064,749,771]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,226,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[209,1360,197,981]" captionTargetId="figure-473@6.[207,1362,195,982]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Schematic distribution of the Unio species in the Western Palaearctic. Points indicate the general vicinity of sampled localities. See Supporting Information, Table S1 for details." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713993/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Fig. S2</figureCitation>
). These two subclades were consistently recovered as distinct species in the bGMYC and M-PTP analyses. From 16 to 22 substitutions separated the Spanish-Moroccan haplotypes from the Tunisian ones. Although the eastern haplotypes were more similar, none of the Spanish, Moroccan and Tunisian specimens shared haplotypes among the 10 detected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[827,1444,197,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">
This species had a rounded shape similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1840" box="[827,936,1025,1046]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Potomida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,936,1025,1046]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">Potomida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but clear diagnostic characters such as the lateral teeth, the umbonal sculpture and shell thickness differentiate the two taxa (
<bibRefCitation author="Araujo R &amp; Toledo C &amp; Machordom A" box="[1206,1436,1086,1108]" pageId="5" pageNumber="280" pagination="131 - 141" refId="ref11862" refString="Araujo R, Toledo C, Machordom A. 2009 a. Redescription of Unio gibbus Spengler, 1793, a west Palaearctic freshwater mussel with hookless glochidia. Malacologia 51: 131 - 141." type="journal article" year="2009">
Araujo 
<emphasis box="[1293,1352,1086,1108]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="280">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009a
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
